'''RADOM''' is a [[Bulgaria]]n [[Liulin]]-type spectrometry-[[dosimetry]] instrument, designed to precisely measure [[Cosmic ray|cosmic radiation]] around the [[Moon]]. It is installed on the Indian [[satellite]] [[Chandrayaan-1]]. Another three instruments were deployed on the [[International Space Station]]. All Liulin-type instruments are designed and build by the Solar-Terrestrial Influences Laboratory at the [[Bulgarian Academy of Sciences]].{{citation needed|date=June 2013}}
